    "template": "content",
    "texts": [
     "{\"template\":\"intro\",\"texts\":[\"The Assisted Transport pilot is a joint customer research project to test ways in which future users of door-to-door services might have more flexibility and choice in how they travel. It is being run by Transport for London in partnership with London Councils.\"],\"link\":{\"image\":{}},\"image\":{},\"wrapped\":false}",
     "The pilot involves 300 randomly selected participants, from amongst Taxicard and Dial-a-Ride users in two London boroughs, Hounslow and Southwark.",
     "We are aiming to offer participants more flexibility and choice over how they can use the Taxicard service. It will be easier for all participants to choose longer distance journeys (as long as they start or finish in a London borough).",
     "As part of the pilot, we will also be trialling two different forms of Taxicard budget. Participants will be offered one of two packages - either based on trips or on a 'virtual cash purse'.",
     "The pilot will first track participants' usual travel behaviour. Then, from April 2019, it will track any changes to their travel that arise after the trial changes to Taxicard are introduced.",
     "We plan to run the pilot until April 2020."
    ],
